      • toBoolean

        @Deprecated
public boolean toBoolean()
        Deprecated. 
        This was a required method in the old SoyData interface. For new data classes, please use interface SoyValue, which has the method coerceToBoolean(). Converts this data object into a boolean (e.g. when used in a boolean context). In other words, this method tells whether this object is truthy.

        The empty string is falsy.

        Specified by:
        toBoolean in class SoyData
        Returns:
        The value of this data object if coerced into a boolean. I.e. true if this object is truthy, false if this object is falsy.
